Functions	aren't	commonly	used	in	pseudo-code,	since	pseudo-code	is	mostly
used	as	a	way	for	programmers	to	sketch	out	program	concepts	before	writing
compilable	code.	Since	pseudo-code	doesn't	actually	have	to	work,	full	functions
don't	need	to	be	written	out—simply	jotting	down	Do	some	complex	stuff	here
will	suffice.	But	in	a	programming	language	like	C,	functions	are	used	heavily.
Most	of	the	real	usefulness	of	C	comes	from	collections	of	existing	functions
called	libraries.

