Strings
The	value	"Hello,	world!\n"	passed	to	the	printf()	function	in	the	previous
program	is	a	string—technically,	a	character	array.	In	C,	an	array	is	simply	a	list
of	n	elements	of	a	specific	data	type.	A	20-character	array	is	simply	20	adjacent
characters	located	in	memory.	Arrays	are	also	referred	to	as	buffers.	The
char_array.c	program	is	an	example	of	a	character	array.
